Texts.Eng: A fellow Avian! Our people may call us Grounded but we sail through the stars now, don't we?
Texts.Rus: Собрат Авиан! Наш народ может называть нас Приземлёнными, но теперь мы ведь путешествуем среди звезд, не так ли?

Texts.Eng: A fellow Hylotl! Be warned, friend - not everyone in space is as cultured as our kind.
Texts.Rus: Собрат Хилотл! Будь осторожен, друг, не все в космосе настолько культурны как наш народ.

Texts.Eng: A get a lot o' strange looks from folks up here. I guess they ain't used to seein' folks like me round these parts.
A word of advice from one Hylotl to another - space is filled with many uncultured individuals.
Texts.Rus: Небольшой совет от одного Хилотла другому — космос наполнен невоспитанными личностями.

Texts.Eng: Among the stars, looking down upon entire worlds, even an oppressive regime can appear small and insignificant.
Texts.Rus: Среди звезд, смотря сверху на целые миры, даже деспотический режим может выглядеть мелким и незначительным.

Texts.Eng: Another Glitch! If you are here, you must also be self-aware. There is strength in numbers, my friend!
Texts.Rus: Еще один Глитч! Если ты здесь, то у тебя тоже есть самосознание. Сила в количестве, мой друг!

Texts.Eng: Are the rumours of space parasites true? I dearly hope not!
Texts.Rus: А слухи о космических паразитах правдивы? Я очень надеюсь что нет!

Texts.Eng: Are you accustomed to sailing the empty vast ocean of space?
Texts.Rus: А Вы привыкли бороздить бескрайний и пустой океан космоса?

Texts.Eng: Before I gained self-awareness, I hunted monsters for my village. Perhaps I shall do the same here in space?
Texts.Rus: Прежде чем у меня появилось самосознание, я охотился на монстров в моей деревне. Возможно мне стоит заняться тем же здесь, в космосе?

Texts.Eng: Bein' glowin' star folk gets you a lot o' weird looks around these parts.
Big Ape doesn't feel so big from up here.
Texts.Rus: Большой Эйп не чувствуется таким большим отсюда.

Texts.Eng: Do you ever get scared that you'll fall into the infinite, empty void of space by accident? I know I do!
Texts.Rus: Тебе никогда не было страшно от мысли, что ты можешь случайно упасть в бесконечную пустоту космоса? А мне было...

Texts.Eng: Floran didn't want to fight and eat all of Floran's life, ssso Floran came to ssspace inssstead.
Texts.Rus: Флоран не хочет провести всю жизнь Флорана между дракой и едой, поэтому Флоран вместо этого прибыл в космоссс.

Texts.Eng: Floran got lossst during hunt and now Floran here. Floran not quite sssure what happened.
Texts.Rus: Флоран потерялссся во время охоты, и теперь Флоран здесссь. Флоран не уверен что произошло.

Texts.Eng: Floran left Floran's tribe because Floran isss pacifist. Floran finding it... Tough.
Texts.Rus: Флоран ушел из племени Флорана, потому что Флоран — пацифист. Флорану... сложно.

Texts.Eng: Floran livesss in sssky. Floran higher up than all of Floran's tribe!
Texts.Rus: Флоран живёт в небе. Флоран вышшше чем все оссстальные из племени Флорана!

Texts.Eng: Floran's Greenfinger taught Floran about ssspace travel. Now Floran livesss in sssky!
Texts.Rus: Древоуст Флорана обучил Флорана о космичессских путешессствиях. Теперь Флоран живет в небе!

Texts.Eng: Floran's name is <selfname>. Floran saying hello!
Texts.Rus: Флорана зовут <selfname>. Флоран говорит привет!

Texts.Eng: Floran's tribe livesss on planet. Tribe doesssn't like Floran's pacifist waysss so Floran comesss here.
Texts.Rus: Племя Флорана живет на планете. Племени не нравится пацифистссский путь Флорана, поэтому Флоран пришел сюда.

Texts.Eng: From up here in space, the entire history of the Avian people feels like merely a footnote in the great tapestry of the universe.
Texts.Rus: Отсюда, из космоса, вся история Авиан выглядит лишь незначительной заметкой на великом гобелене вселенной.

Texts.Eng: Glowin' like an oil lamp really helps yer stand out in space, don't yer agree?
Texts.Rus: Светиться как масляная лампа и правда помогает не теряться на фоне космоса, согласен?

Texts.Eng: Glowin' star folk like us get a lot o' weird looks around these parts.
Greetings, fellow Apex. Are you in outer space for any specific purpose?
Texts.Rus: Приветствую, друг Апекс. Ты путешествуешь по космосу с какой-то конкретной целью?

Texts.Eng: Greetings. Are you in outer space for any specific purpose?
Texts.Rus: Привет. Ты путешествуешь по космосу с какой-то конкретной целью?

Texts.Eng: Have you always known about space travel? Did you always dream about venturing through the stars?
Texts.Rus: Всегда ли ты знал о путешествиях в космосе? Всегда ли мечтал углубиться в звёздные дали?

Texts.Eng: Hello, stranger! I hope you've been vaccinated against space parasites lately!
Hey there! My name is <selfname>. I've been here a while, to say the least.
Hey, what's the weather outside like? It's still night-time, right?
I actually don't know if we have to dress like this - I'm just doing it to fit in.
I am meant to be fighting the Miniknog alongside my fellow rebels, but right now I am merely procrastinating.
I don't trust living on planets anymore, especially after what happened to Earth...
I have come to space to find a professional trade. One day I shall be <selfname>, master engineer!
I have come to space to find artistic inspiration among the stars...
I heard that the Miniknog have their own spacefaring mechs... This cannot be true, can it...?
I hope that by exiling myself to space, the Miniknog will not come looking for me.
I hope you aren't planning on visiting Earth right now because I have some bad news...
I hope you aren't secretly working for the Stargazers! The shackles of false faith shall not chain me again.
I may already be incredibly intelligent, but there is potentially even more to learn out here in space!
I spend much of my life not knowing space even existed, and now I am here!
I thought I'd be free from dangerous monsters when I came to space, but now I hear there are space monsters as well?!
If space is like a grand ocean, perhaps it too is home to gargantuan beasts?
In space, no one can hear you... Complain that you're bored.
Is it night-time outside? Haha, just kidding. It's always night in space!
It ain't easy to blend in around these parts when you light up like a summer afternoon.
It is said that most people cannot comprehend the vastness of space. Fortunately, I am intelligent enough to do so.
My name is <selfname> - it is a pleasure to make you acquaintance.
My people used to believe the stars were the many eyes of their god, Kluex. Science, well, says otherwise.
My scientific knowledge is more valuable out here in space than under the opressive regime of the Miniknog.
Nice t' meet y'all, space cowboy!
Now I am in space, I feel so miniscule. How will I make my mark when I matter so little?
One day I shall explore the cosmos instead of hanging about here... But today is not that day.
One day I'll have my own ship and crew! Captain <selfname> has a nice ring to it, don't you think?
One of the small benefits of life in space is that fleas don't survive easily out here...
Other Floran! Floran likesss similar faces.
Our people used to believe the stars were the many eyes of Kluex. Science, well, says otherwise.
Space is an ocean of sorts. In some small way, it makes me feel at home.
Space is the real wild country, ain't it? Bandits to hunt, bars to drink at... It sure is the life!
The Apex can seek solace out here, among the stars. I welcome a quiet life.
The empty blackness of space is like a blank canvas. How I wish I could somehow paint upon it.
The first step towards fighting a dictatorship is to learn. The enemy can take your weapons, but never your knowledge.
The great thing about living in space is that there's always room. Infinite room, in fact.
The low-moisture atmosphere in space is good for preventing rust.
The most terrifying aspect of the Miniknog regime is that the Apex people are comfortable with the cycle of oppression.
The most terrifying aspect of the Miniknog regime is that the our people are comfortable with the cycle of oppression.
The planets sail across the infinite night, like fish in a grand ocean.
The planets that many warmongering civilisations have fought wars over seem so small from up here, do they not?
The stars really call out t' me. I guess it jus' feels right bein' up here, closer to 'em.
There ain't no law in space. That's purty ideal for rogues an' villains, ain't it?
There is always new knowledge to find. I have come to space to learn more about our universe.
To be so small compared to the great scale of all existence... Does space also make you feel insignificant?
To fly through space on board a ship... It isn't like having real wings, but it's close!
To my people, space travel is viewed as a gift from Kluex to help spread our faith. To me, it is a gift for discovery and knowledge!
To our people, space travel is viewed as a gift from Kluex to help spread our faith. To me, it is a gift for discovery and knowledge!
Us Apex can seek solace out here, among the stars. I welcome a quiet life.
Welcome to... Space! Are you new here?
Welcome, fellow Glitch! I am <selfname>. I wish you well on your travels.
Welcome, friend. If you are here, then perhaps you too have evaded the clutches of the Miniknog?
Welcome, spacefarer! I am <selfname>. I wish you well on your travels.
Welcome, stranger! As sure as the suns rise shall I greet every new face with a smile.
Well ruffle my feathers - a friendly new face!
What secrets are hidden among the stars? I very much desire to find out.
You ain't gonna look me in the eyes, partner? I'm jus' foolin' with yer - I ain't got any eyes!
You have a look about you - A look of... Wanderlust?
You know, it's really hard to maintain a sleep cycle when there's no days or nights.
You'd think that living offworld would get lonely, but... Well, you'd be right, actually.
